title: Thanks for the tolls!
text:
I just wanted to say Thanks to the developers for allowing the app to put me on a toll road EVEN THOUGH I had the option to avoid tolls checked. By the time I realized what was happening, I couldn‚Äôt change course. 

It couldn‚Äôt be avoided because I don‚Äôt know the area, which is I was using Google Maps in the first place. I also don‚Äôt have an EZ-Pass in my car because I hate paying tolls on principle. 

I‚Äôm in a metropolitan area where toll times change depending on rush hour. It would be nice if the almighty Google kept up with the times. 

I‚Äôll be sending my toll bill to Google when it arrives.

title: Excellent Service
text:
I can‚Äôt say enough positive things about Venom‚Äô service and parts departments.
I had an unusual situation which is too long to share.
Bottom line is everyone I spoke to at Venom was very nice, patient, and extremely helpful. To help me resolve my issue I was asked to send pictures. To help me understand what I needed to do, Venom sent me pictures and they called me to further help me. 
Their whole team was very friendly, very polite, very prompt, and very helpful.
They did exactly what they said they were going to do and promised to help me, which they did.
I received the parts I needed in a timely fashion, but more important I feel I received good old fashioned customer service.
Hats off to Venom!!!!

title: Ketchum Roofing & Windows
text: Just had our home and garage roofed by Ketchum.  We are new to the area having lived here only a few months.  Chase took charge when he discovered wind and hail damage. He contacted State Farm and handle everything.  We had to do very little and all the work only cost us was our deductible.  The work was great, the crew great, they cleaned everything up like they had never been here. They came back twice the day after they finished to check and make sure we were happy and satisfied.  If you need roofing, call these folks you want be sorry.
